```
function q = euler2quat(euler)
% Convert Euler angles to quaternion
%
% Inputs:
%   euler - Nx3 array of Euler angles [roll, pitch, yaw] (radians)
%
% Outputs:
%   q - Nx4 array of quaternions [w, x, y, z]

% Calculate trig values
cy = cos(euler(:,3) * 0.5);
sy = sin(euler(:,3) * 0.5);
cp = cos(euler(:,2) * 0.5);
sp = sin(euler(:,2) * 0.5);
cr = cos(euler(:,1) * 0.5);
sr = sin(euler(:,1) * 0.5);

% Calculate quaternion components
q = [cy.*cp.*cr+sy.*sp.*sr, ...
     cy.*cp.*sr-sy.*sp.*cr, ...
     cy.*sp.*cr+sy.*cp.*sr, ...
     sy.*cp.*cr-cy.*sp.*sr];
end
```

Note: euler input is a Nx3 array of euler angles [roll, pitch, yaw] (radians) and the output is a Nx4 array of quaternions [w, x, y, z].

Here is an optimized version of the Euler angle to quaternion conversion function in MATLAB that uses element-wise operations and vectorization for faster execution:

